The paper deals with information theory and communication systems, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. The use of cooperation and partial cribbing also involves networked systems and protocols, which could place it in the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of coding and decoding techniques, which could place it in the cs.SI (Systems and Control) sub-category. The use of joint typicality decoding and Gaussian MACs suggests that it could also belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the study of capacity regions, which could place it in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category.
